<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFF68FC5FFD724EA5" authority="LeConte, 1847" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1847" box="[151,670,951,977]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFF68FC5FFD724EA5" bold="true" box="[151,670,951,977]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFF68FC5FFE224EA5" bold="true" box="[151,462,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pseudocanthon perplexus</emphasis>
(LeConte, 
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFDA5FC5FFD7A4EA5" box="[602,662,951,977]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1847.0">1847</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36CAAF37FFBBFF68FBEAFF0D4B50" blockId="10.[151,1436,1026,1572]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
A series of specimens of this widespread mainland species (Arizona to Indiana, south to 
<collectingCountry id="F302765AAF37FFBBFB48FBEAFAEC4968" box="[1207,1280,1026,1052]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) from Grand 
<collectingCountry id="F302765AAF37FFBBFF68FBC2FF1B4930" box="[151,247,1066,1092]" name="Bahamas" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Bahama</collectingCountry>
<collectingCountry id="F302765AAF37FFBBFEFEFBC2FEA04930" box="[257,332,1066,1092]" name="Iceland" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Island</collectingCountry>
, Freeport, were taken 
<date id="FFAB100AAF37FFBBFDA5FBC2FCCB4930" box="[602,807,1066,1092]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1987-06-20" valueMax="1987-06-27" valueMin="1987-06-20">
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFDA5FBC2FD4F4930" box="[602,675,1066,1092]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="23.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="20.0">20–27</number>
June 
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFD13FBC2FCCB4930" box="[748,807,1066,1092]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</date>
by W. E. Steiner, M. J. and R. Molineaux (
<collectionCode id="ED04AE0FAF37FFBBFAC6FBC2FA7B4930" box="[1337,1431,1066,1092]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">NMNH</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED04AE0FAF37FFBBFF68FBBAFF094918" box="[151,229,1106,1132]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mzn7-y8yj" name="West Indian Beetle Fauna Project Collection" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">WIBF</collectionCode>
). This is apparently the first report of 
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFD4DFBBBFCD34918" box="[690,831,1107,1132]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. p e r p l e x u s</emphasis>
from the West Indies, and given its dung requirements (
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFF13FB92FE6E49E0" author="Blume" box="[236,386,1146,1172]" pageId="10" pageNumber="13" refString="Blume, R. R. (1982) Description of larva and notes on biology of Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte) (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 36, 250 - 254." type="journal article" year="1982">
Blume 
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFEBCFB92FE6E49E0" box="[323,386,1146,1172]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), almost certainly represents a recent arrival on Grand 
<collectingCountry id="F302765AAF37FFBBFBFFFB92FB8849E0" box="[1024,1124,1146,1172]" name="Bahamas" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Bahama</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFB91FB93FA7049E0" box="[1134,1436,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFB91FB93FA7049E0" box="[1134,1436,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pseudocanthon perplexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all previously recorded West Indian 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFD24FB4BFC7C49C8" box="[731,912,1187,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFD24FB4BFC7C49C8" box="[731,912,1187,1212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pseudocanthon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFC12FB4BFB0E49C8" authority="Bates" authorityName="Bates" box="[1005,1250,1186,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorizans">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFC12FB4BFB6949C8" box="[1005,1157,1187,1212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. chlorizans</emphasis>
(Bates)
</taxonomicName>
(recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F302765AAF37FFBBFF68FB22FF1D4990" box="[151,241,1226,1252]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and the southernmost Lesser Antilles [
<collectingCountry id="F302765AAF37FFBBFD3AFB22FCC04990" box="[709,812,1226,1252]" name="Grenada" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Grenada</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F302765AAF37FFBBFC96FB22FBF74990" box="[873,1051,1226,1252]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">the Grenadines</collectingCountry>
of Union, Carriacou, Mustique, and Bequia], 
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFEC7FB1AFE1E4878" author="Matthews" box="[312,498,1266,1292]" pageId="10" pageNumber="13" refString="Matthews, E. G. (1966) A taxonomic and zoogeographic survey of the Scarabaeinae of the Antilles (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Society, 21, 1 - 134." type="journal article" year="1966">
Matthews 
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFE4AFB1AFE1E4878" box="[437,498,1266,1292]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1966.0">1966</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFDFFFB1AFD174878" author="Woodruff" box="[512,763,1266,1292]" pageId="10" pageNumber="14" refString="Woodruff, R. E., Beck B. M., Skelley P. E., Schotman C. Y. L. &amp; Thomas M. C. (1998) Checklist and bibliography of the insects of Grenada and the Grenadines. Center for Systematic Entomology, Memoirs, 2, 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="1998">
Woodruff 
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFD85FB1BFD5A4878" box="[634,694,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFD40FB1AFD174878" box="[703,763,1266,1292]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) in lacking a basal carina on the pygidium. It should be noted that 
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFEDEFAF2FE0D4840" author="Howden" box="[289,481,1306,1332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="13" refString="Howden, H. F. (1966) Notes on Canthonini of the &quot; Biologia Centrali-Americana &quot; and descriptions of the new species (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 98, 725 - 741." type="journal article" year="1966">
Howden (
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFE64FAF2FE344840" box="[411,472,1306,1332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFDD6FAF2FD1B4840" author="Woodruff" box="[553,759,1306,1332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="14" refString="Woodruff, R. M. (1973) Scarab Beetles of Florida (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) Part I, the Laparosticti (Subfamilies Scarabaeinaea, Aphodiinae, Hybosorinae, Ochodaeinae, Geotrupinae, Acanthocerinae). Arthropods of Florida and Neighboring Land Areas. Florida Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services, Gainesville, 8: i - xi + 1 - 220." type="journal article" year="1973">
Woodruff (
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFD4EFAF2FD024840" box="[689,750,1306,1332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1973.0">1973</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
both raised the question of validity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFB09FAF3FA794840" box="[1270,1429,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorizans">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFB09FAF3FA794840" box="[1270,1429,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. chlorizans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFF68FAABFE294828" box="[151,453,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFF68FAABFE294828" box="[151,453,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pseudocanthon perplexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is purported to differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFCF7FAABFC734828" box="[776,927,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorizans">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFCF7FAABFC734828" box="[776,927,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. chlorizans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the denser pronotal punctures, in which the discal punctures are separated by 1.0–1.5 diameters, compared with the 2.0 or more diameters that separate them in 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFED5FA7BFD6C48D8" authority="Howden 1966" authorityName="Howden" authorityYear="1966" box="[298,640,1426,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorizans">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFED5FA7BFE2D48D8" box="[298,449,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. chlorizans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFE2FFA7AFD9448D8" author="Howden" box="[464,632,1426,1452]" pageId="10" pageNumber="13" refString="Howden, H. F. (1966) Notes on Canthonini of the &quot; Biologia Centrali-Americana &quot; and descriptions of the new species (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 98, 725 - 741." type="journal article" year="1966">
Howden 
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFDC3FA7AFD9448D8" box="[572,632,1426,1452]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1966.0">1966</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The pronotum in 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFCA4FA7BFC1E48D8" box="[859,1010,1427,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorizans">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFCA4FA7BFC1E48D8" box="[859,1010,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. chlorizans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also said to be much shinier, with the punctures simple, while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFDFEFA53FD7C48A0" box="[513,656,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFDFEFA53FD7C48A0" box="[513,656,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. perplexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pronotal punctures are larger, microumbiculate in appearance, and the surface less shining (
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFE15FA0AFD7A4888" author="Howden" box="[490,662,1506,1532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="13" refString="Howden, H. F. (1966) Notes on Canthonini of the &quot; Biologia Centrali-Americana &quot; and descriptions of the new species (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 98, 725 - 741." type="journal article" year="1966">
Howden 
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFDA8FA0AFD7A4888" box="[599,662,1506,1532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1966.0">1966</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B3BAF37FFBBFD55FA0AFCA14888" author="Blume" box="[682,845,1506,1532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="13" refString="Blume, R. R. (1982) Description of larva and notes on biology of Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte) (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 36, 250 - 254." type="journal article" year="1982">
Blume (
<number id="3DDD24EDAF37FFBBFCF7FA0AFCA94888" box="[776,837,1506,1532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the larva and biology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D49AF37FFBBFB11FA0BFA924888" box="[1262,1406,1507,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="B961EAD8AF37FFBBFB11FA0BFA924888" box="[1262,1406,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. perplexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Texas.
</paragraph>
